cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ADAAD in your research, please cite it using the metadata in this file."

type: software

title: "ADAAD: Autonomous Device-Anchored Adaptive Development"
version: "3.5.0"
date-released: "2026-03-09"

abstract: >
  ADAAD is an open-source autonomous code mutation system with constitutional
  governance enforcement. Three Claude-powered AI agents (Architect, Dream, Beast)
  propose code improvements that compete via a genetic algorithm (BLX-alpha crossover).
  Fittest candidates advance to a 16-rule constitutional gate — a fail-closed policy
  engine evaluated in strict topological order. All governance decisions are recorded
  in a SHA-256 hash-chained append-only evidence ledger. Every decision supports
  deterministic replay: given the same epoch state, the same governance evaluation
  is always produced. Self-calibrating scoring weights adapt via momentum gradient
  descent across epochs. The system implements a novel "constitutional architecture"
  pattern in which governance enforcement is a structural invariant rather than a
  configurable policy — no code path bypassing the gate exists.

